<item>
            <title>[JDK-8299259] C2: Div/Mod nodes without zero check could be split through iv phi of loop resulting in SIGFPE</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8299259</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8248552&quot; title=&quot;C2 crashes with SIGFPE due to division by zero&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8248552&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8248552&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added bailout code when trying to split DivI/ModI nodes without zero check (control is NULL) through an iv phi which has an input that contains zero in its type range.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
However, the fix is not complete in two regards:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1) We could have an &amp;quot;iv phi -&amp;gt; X -&amp;gt; DivI/ModI&amp;quot; chain where we want to split X and DivI/ModI through the iv phi. In this case, we first split X and create a new phi to merge the newly created nodes for X. When splitting the DivI/ModI node afterwards, the bailout code finds the newly created phi as divisor input which is not the iv phi and we do not bail out. We should change that.&lt;br/&gt;
2) Since &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8256655&quot; title=&quot;rework long counted loop handling&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8256655&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8256655&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we also optimize iv phis of long counted loops. The earlier added bailout code, however, only handles int divisions/modulo. We should extend the bailout code to additionally handle DivL/ModL. </description>
